      <h2>The Gaps That Hurt Agencies Are Almost Always the Ones Nobody Was Looking For</h2>
      <p>Independent agencies run lean. That means tech stacks that get set up once and forgotten. Security settings from a previous employee. A website that used to convert leads but stopped somewhere along the way. Tools that are paid for but not actually used.</p>
      <p>None of it feels like a crisis &mdash; until it is.</p>
      <p>Carrier cyber requirements are tightening. Compliance expectations are increasing. And the agencies that get caught flat-footed aren&rsquo;t the ones ignoring the problem on purpose &mdash; they&rsquo;re the ones who just never had a clear picture of where they stood.</p>
